animal.description:
Bane, Male, 6yrs, Staffordshire Bull Terrier, Tri color, 60lbs

Bane is nothing short of personality, always happy to give you a big smile. He loves to be on the go, but is often happy for a good romp in the yard. Pretty much if his humans are doing it, he is down for it.and at the end of the day, he is happy to settle in for some couch time and a good cuddle.

Bane is crate trained and has good house manners. He knows his basic obedience and loves to learn. 

Bane gets along with dogs medium and up, though he can be overwhelming for some dogs. True to the Terrier in him, he has prey drive. So small dogs cats and other creatures of small and furry variety are a no go for him. Bane does love humans of both the large an small variety, he just requires that they adore him too. 

This boy has energy to burn and can be high drive. So daily exercise is an absolute must. He needs a 6 foot privacy fence to keep him safe. Our bully breed adoption guidelines apply.

Bane is ready to find his Happy Ever After, if you feel it may be with you and submit an application. 

Bane's adoption fee is 250.00 and he is fully vetted

Adopter must be local to the Saint Louis Metro area.

Interested adopters must submit an adoption application through our website, steppingstonebully.org to be considered.

Pixie is a member of the Dolly Goodpuppy longtimer's club who is hoping 2019 is the year she finds her forever home.

Pixie has been with us since she was just a pup and is repeatedly overlooked by adopters as she is timid around new people. It takes her a little bit to adjust and be comfortable with strangers but once she does, she is as happy as can be. Being shy is Pixie's only fault; she is playful, fun, spunky, loving, overall a nice medium-sized terrier mix who plays well with other dogs. Pixie would benefit from a home with a confident dog and patient humans to help her overcome some of her shyness. In fact, a family willing to spend time with her at the kennel would be ideal.

We really would love for Pixie to find a family where she will be loved, adored, spoiled, and finally know what "home" feels like.

Pixie is crate trained, up to date on shots, spayed, microchipped, and current on heartworm/flea/tick prevention.

Interested in fostering or adopting? complete our application at dollygoodpuppy.org

PLEASE NOTE: At this time we are unable to adopt out of state and are not accepting applicants located outside of Georgia.

animal.description:
Hi my name is Chunk and I am an American Bulldog, Staffordshire mix. I am known as an AMERICAN BULLY.
 I am a short dog, but I weigh over 75 lbs. I was recently surrendered to Valhalla Rescue with my friend, when my people moved and could not take me with them. I am friendly with other dogs that are friendly with me, but i do better with girl dogs. I love people, but I do need a little slow introduction because before I came in to rescue I spent my entire life in a fenced backyard with little interaction with new people. But I do love the way everybody's been so nice to me and it only takes me a couple minutes to warm up to you

The rescue has really helped me come a long way. I had yeast infections in my ears and on my skin, I had bad eye lids called entropia which is common for the breed, they neutered me and gave me all my vaccines. I am doing so much better now and I'm ready to find my new forever home. I've been okay with cats so far but no one has left me alone with them yet and I like kids but sometimes I can get a little excited and may knock one over because I weigh so much.

My adoption fee is $300 and it helps to ensure that Valhalla Rescue can continue to help dogs like me. A wonderful group of people dedicated to helping dogs with medical conditions get the treatments they need and then find their forever homes. Without them I would still be in bad condition in someone's backyard.

 If you are interested in adopting me visit their website and submit an online application. Www.valhallarescue.org.  you can also call them at 360-559-4972 for more information.

Thank you so much for taking a look at me and I look forward to meeting you soon!!!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.UPDATE: Sienna has greatly improved! She's walking albeit a little stiff legged. She runs and walks and she doesn't seem to be in any pain. She doesn't realize that she has a handicap and everyday we see improvement. She is now ready for her forever home.Sienna was surrendered to a local shelter and pulled by a good Samaritan with the intention of finding a rescue. We were eventually contacted and Sienna became an ATDR dog in July! The vet specialist believes she was hit by a car and is very wobbly in her rear. Originally what the shelter thought was IVDD or a back injury appears to be the aftermath of some kind of trauma. She is learning to walk again and very unsteady on her feet thus far. She will be receiving special cold laser treatments and accupunture to try to get her to bounce back from her injuries and possibly walk again. Please say a prayer for this beautiful girl that she will one day walk without problems and find a home to love her forever! If you'd like to sponsor this baby by making a small monthly donation for her laser treatments there is a donation button on our home page. We have seen some improvement on her laser treatments.
2017 UPDATE: Sienna aka Miss Wiggles is in a new foster home. She got her nick name on her first day because when her foster put a slip leash on her to take her out for a walk, it took exactly 2 seconds for her to wiggle out of it. Sienna is an energetic, happy, sweet baby who doesn't know she has a disability. She races around the house playing with her Doxie friends and the cats in her foster home. She is head strong and pushes her way to the front of the line for dinner and for pats and loving. This girl doesn't want to be left out of anything and doesn't want to be left alone. She's good with cats, good with dogs both small and large, and probably would be good with children.

Sparky was rescued after the flood receded. He wondered into a local fire department covered in mud, soaking wet & trailing a cut rope. We believe he was left tied outside most of his life. Sparky does well in the car, likes toys, playful, affectionate & goofy. We believe Sparky to be a Shepherd/Lab mix, approximately 4yrs 7month old(June), approximately 64lbs(July), neutered, microchip, current on age appropriate vaccinations & working on finishing his house training. He is good with kids, other dogs & even cats! Sparky wold do best in a home with another dog for him to play with. Please consider opening your heart & home to Sparky.

If you would like more information on this dog please contact Apaws at info@apawspets.org

animal.description:
Due to the COVID-19 pandemic and to maintain social distancing requirements, appointments are required. Please EMAIL apassionforpaws@gmail.com and wait for confirmation of your appointment before coming to visit the Akita Ranch. We also request that visitors wear masks. located in Romoland CAA little rough around the edges, Cedar is a mix of confident gentleman meets backyard bruiser, but he is mostly misunderstood. Cedar was in an abusive home before coming to the Akita Ranch which is why he can still have some trust issues in new situations. But deep down he is much more refined and likes to take care of his own. Working with him during his time at the ranch we have seen much growth from some of the issues he had when he arrived: he can be food aggressive but has learned to trust with his food if you give him space and a safe place to eat, he is selective with people he meets but is very willing to follow the lead of a person he trusts. He is very responsive to a respectful, loving person who is willing to train him with consistent positive reinforcement training and give him his space when he needs it. Once he feels safe, he will come to you on his own and loves scratches and affection. Due to humans who broke his trust many times, for a time, he will keep an eye on you until he sees that you are dependable and he then begins to let down his guard. Cedar is a noble, honest, character and one of the greatest personalities at the ranch. He really wants to make his people happy but needs time and patience to continue to overcome the pain from his past. He walks well on leash, loves going for car rides, is very well-mannered at the park and in new situations if his person understands his limits and respects his fears. If you have patience and a tender heart, and are willing to help him work through his past, Cedar would love to grow with you and see what this great big world has to offer!

Come meet debonair Cedar at Akita Ranch 28930 Ellis Ave, Romoland, CA (open 10-5, 7 days)

animal.description:
Due to COVID-19, our Sanctuary is temporarily closed, with a small number of staff running our daily operations. For this reason, we are suspending  adoptions and tours for an undetermined amount of time. While we will try to respond to emails and phone calls as best we can, we do not have a dedicated office staff and are prioritizing the care of our animals and health of our staff.

We want to thank you for your understanding, patience, and support during this time. 

Hutch was a transfer from the SFSPCA with his brother Rickie. They were overwhelmed by the noise and activity of the city and needed a quiet place to decompress and process all the changes in their life. Hutch is a shy, funny and quirky dog who loves treats and curling up in a warm and comfy bed. He would do best in a quiet predictable home. He frequently stays in the sanctuary manager's office during the day and is happy to nap away the day on a couch or in an ex pen with other small dogs. If you are looking for a small dog with low exercise needs and a cat-like personality, Hutch may be your guy!



All of our animals are up-to-date on their vaccinations, spayed/neutered, microchipped, and have had a physical exam. At adoption we provide: veterinary records and vaccine certificates, castration certificate, lifetime lost animal support, one month’s worth of flea medication and heartworm medication, one week’s worth of food, a leash, a collar, an ID tag, and a familiar toy or blanket to help them settle in. We also provide lifetime basic positive training support.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Pupdate 6-17-2016

 I have been in my foster home for five days now. Foster mom thinks it would be best if my mom and I are adopted out as a bonded pair. We are pretty much inseparable and I have been with Tiffin (my mommy) all of my life. If mommy can't see me, she starts crying and searching all over. I am so happy that foster mom and dad have discovered this, we will be together always and forever.

 My name is Taffy and I'm a very small Coated Xolo. My coloring is remarkable, I am a bowl of ice cream sundae for your eyes! A little bit of this and a little bit of that and you get a beautiful girl like me. I have stunning eyes and a beautiful coat. I get along with other pups, but when it's feeding time, I need to be crated to eat because I just might eat someone else's food and I will let everyone know what my intentions are.

 I came from Mexico where my previous owners wanted me to be euthanized. They didn't want us anymore. My goodness, I'm only two years old and deserve far better than that!A very nice lady came to my mommy's (Tiffin) and my rescue and saved us from sure death. This nice lady brought us all the way to the United States so we have a better chance of being adopted to a loving family.

 I love other pups as long as I am introduced to them slowly. I was bred to hunt squirrels, so I need to stay on my leash at all times while I'm out for a walk. I do need a fenced in backyard, and it must be secure. I can jump pretty high and I can run fast!

 I saw my doctor today, I am HW negative, UTD on all of my vaccinations, spayed and microchipped. I am ready for my forever home! I couldn't possibly be any more healthy than I am now.

 I love people, I love to give kisses and I make the perfect lap pup. It did take me a small minute to warm up to my foster daddy, but we are inseparable now. No small children for me, I am very fine boned and need older children that can respect my small stature. I'm a lion in a small package!

animal.description:
Thunder is a handsome 7 year old WOLF DOG Shepherd/ Malamute mix. He can be aloof and standoffish with strangers, but very affection when he warms up, to the point of being a big goofball! Thunder is a quick learner and knows several commands including sit, down, and spin. He is a very high energy dog and would do best with an experienced, confident owner willing to participate in activities like walking, jogging, and hiking. 

Thunder can be food aggressive, especially over raw food but he is currently being worked with regarding this. He will need an experienced owner that would know what to expect with him. Routine and consistency is key with Thunder. He was not socialized to other dogs until he arrived at our rescue, and we have noticed he is awkward around other dogs and has problems communicating, but has not shown any real aggression. He requires a fenced in outdoor enclosure that is at least six feet in height. He was raised inside, but would not settle down or relax in the house and get into everything.

Please no small pets such as small dogs or cats. Thunder is part wolf and will only be adopted to areas where wolfdogs are legal to own. 

If you're interested in Thunder, please read our adoption requirements first at; http://www.howlingwoods.org/adopt_a_wolf_adoption_requirements.html

then submit an application at; http://www.howlingwoods.org/wolf_adoption_adopt_a_wolf_application.php

or contact us by calling (732) 534-5745

Do not inquire about or apply for Thunder if you live in any the following States: Delaware, Maryland, Pennsylvania, New York, Connecticut, Massachusetts, Maine.  Wolfdogs are illegal to possess in these States.

My name is SANDMAN and I'm a handsome 9 yr M Tan Amstaff/Lab/Hound X. I'm 65 lbs of PURE SWEETHEART. I'm the victim of a new baby and my owners have no time for me and they feel I would be better with a person/couple that will have the time to give me daily interactivity that I am not getting. My only vice is that I'm a bit "food funny" and also like to GUARD MY TOYS so I need someone EXPERIENCED with RESOURCE GUARDING. I am fine with other dogs but am a bit dominant so I would be best with a submissive large dog or tough small dog but of course I would be happiest as your "one and only". Unfortunately I'm NOT GOOD with CATS. I'm a great dog for someone that needs a 4 legged Companion to hang with.   Pls come meet me today!

animal.description:
**WE ARE IN DESPERATE NEED OF FOSTER HOMES AT THIS TIME**  Homeward Bound Dog Rescue is an all volunteer rescue organization and all our dogs and puppies are in foster homes - we are not a shelter and do NOT have a facility. For adoption information go to: www.homewardbounddogrescue.com.  You must fill out an application online as we do NOT accept applications at our clinics.

Hi there, I am Morgana, a 30-pound female Feist/Hound mix, possibly Mountain Cur.  I’m about 6 years old.  I have an old leg injury, most likely from being shot since I do have numerous birdshot showing on X-ray.  I can run and jump similar to other dogs.  I am very playful with people and chew toys.  I love to steal the chew toys from my foster brothers but I don’t really play with my foster brothers.  I have a sense of humor and I am happy most of the time; sometimes I have irritable moments, which might be PTSD.  I cannot be crated and I’m unable to walk up stairs due to knee issues.  I do have accidents if I’m not let out routinely; so before bed and before you leave, you have to make sure I relieve myself.  I love car rides.  My foster parents say I am a perfect little girl despite my few issues.  I love to be hugged, petted, and have my tummy rubbed. So come and see me soon and see if I'm the perfect girl for you.
 

We are presently not holding our regular Saturday adoption clinics due to the Covid-19 virus. We are operating on a limited basis until further notice, but we are still adopting dogs out. We require an approved application before we consider anyone for an adoption - so filling out the application is your first step. Different dogs and puppies go up for adoption EVERY WEEK so please feel free to visit the site and click on the Petfinder link for updates. Puppies and dogs up to 2 years old are $350. Dogs over 2 years old are $250. 100% of the adoption fees go to help us save more dogs.

animal.description: May 2020.   Smokey was one of 21 small dogs rescued way back in November 2009.  FFL took 17 on November 22 of 2009 and acquired the other 4 over the next couple months. 17 of the dogs were sent to Save a Dog rescue in Sudbury, MA, over the following months and were adopted (THANK YOU, SAD!).  Smokey is right around 15 lbs. He's a little long in the back and short in the leg. He's listed as Special Needs because of his lack of socialization (but he would come around pretty quickly if he was with dogs that liked attention from people). He's also Special Needs because he lost an eye in November, no idea what happened, but it could be genetic because Oscar (a possible littermate to Smokey) lost both eyes 2 years ago to the same symptoms, also undetermined as to the cause. ??  Smokey is available for adoption ONLY to a person, couple, or family with at least one other dog that he can buddy with, because he's used to being around other dogs (NO CATS); and he, she, or they must have the patience and the time to work with him AND keep him the rest of his life so he doesn't have to be traumatized by more change.  He's also available as a Sponsor Dog.  Please contact FFL at wvcompanions@yahoo.com or call 304 667-1387 and leave a message if you would like information on becoming a much-needed faithful Sponsor.  This info used to be on FFL's Home Page on Petfinder, but sadly, the Home Page was done away with. FFL finally has a website at friendsforlifewv.org but we're just getting it started.  (NOTE: The picture of the four dogs- Skip, Newt, Oscar and Smokey from left to right- was taken in May of 2011.

animal.description: MAY 2020:    Oscar (a.k.a. Little O, Oscadoosky) was one of 21 small dogs rescued way back in November 2009. The owner had begun with a male and a female (possible littermates) 4 years prior but had never had them fixed. The other 21 dogs came from those first two, and we assumed that most of the dogs were inbred. Some were obviously not socialized and were feral. Sadly, the owner, who'd been hospitalized, passed away a couple days after the dogs were removed from the home and we weren't able to get any information about the dogs. 17 of the 21 dogs were accepted and placed through Save A Dog rescue in Sudbury, MA, over the next year (THANK YOU, SAD!).  Oscar is around 14 lbs and is listed as Special Needs because he is feral, and now because he has no eyes. Both eyes were removed in Feb 2017.  No infection was seen, and we have no idea what happened. (It may be a genetic thing, because in Nov 2019, Smokey- a littermate or close relative- also developed the same symptoms in his left eye, and after treatment failed, lost that eye.) Oscar has done very well, and gets around well.  He's available for SPONSORSHIP ONLY, because of his age now (possibly 12-15 years), being feral, and his handicap. He's been at FFL for 11 years now.  (NOTE: The picture of the four dogs- Skip, Newt, Oscar and Smokey from left to right- was taken in May of 2011, as was the close-up.) The one of him with the blue E-collar and the flaps over both eyes was taken 02/03/2017 during the treatment before we had to resort to surgery.  The one of his shaved eye area is the day after the surgery to remove the eyes, and the other two (poor quality!) pictures are more recent. He's hard to photograph; he never stops moving and does NOT want to be handled.  Please contact FFL at wvcompanions@yahoo.com or call 304 667-1387 and leave a message if you'd like information on becoming a Sponsor. Thank you!

animal.description:
Name: Rex & Rocko
Breed: American Bully (Rex) & American Pit Bull Terrier/Lab (Rocko)
Age: Adult
Gender: Males

Rex and Rocko, more affectionately known as “The Boyfriends”, are two best friend bully breed mixes who love each other more than anything in this world.  They may not really be attached at the hip but they sure act like it!  They are seeking a home looking for 2 dogs who already adore each other, get along perfectly, and who are better dogs when they’re together.  While they came into rescue separately-Rocko an owner surrender when his owner went to jail, Rex from a local shelter who didn’t feel he was placeable due to his separation anxiety-they found each other in rescue and instantly became inseparable.  Rocko loves to swim and could spend hours in the pool while Rex is content to lay next to the pool and be the lifeguard. They love to play fetch, though for Rex its not so much fetch as grab the ball and forget to keep it in his mouth on the run back, but Rocko is always happy to pick up the dropped ball and carry it back for his friend.  He’s got Rex’s back after all. They have similar good qualities.  They’re friendly, love people, playful, love to chomp on bones, excellent walking buddies, housetrained, know basic obedience and tricks, and are always down for a good snuggle. They also struggle with separation anxiety.  Separately they struggle far more than when they are together so they actually do make each other better dogs but separation anxiety is an uphill battle that takes patience, consistency, training, and a forever home willing to commit for the long haul and put the time and work in.  They need a home willing to continue to work with them, invest in a sturdy, reinforced crate, and someone who is home more often than not.  We know it is a tall order to find them a home together at all let alone with their separation anxiety but we owe it to them to try to keep this pair together.  These boys have some of the kindest hearts we have ever known.

Requirements: Adopter must own home due to breed mix.  Someone home more often than not, willing to invest in an "indestructible" kennel, and will continue training for the separation anxiety.  No cats.

Interested in adopting?  Fill out a preadopt application here: https://form.jotform.com/203104540557144

You can email laurahhk9@gmail.com with questions and for a preadopt application. This dog has been spayed/neutered, vaccinated as age appropriate, tested for heartworm disease if age appropriate, and dewormed.

animal.description:
Savannah is a Hound/Boxer mix. Savannah has lived in the same home since she was a puppy, but they recently had to give her up due to some family issues and no fault of her own, so poor Savannah has found herself without a "fur"-ever home. Savannah is up to date on vaccines, is Heartworm negative, and spayed. We will cover a microchip for her as well upon adoption. 

Savannah's approx. DOB is 3/25/2010.

Savannah has a good amount of energy (that's a Hound/boxer mix for you) and she loves zipping around the yard, so she would probably do best in an medium/active home that can give her lots of love and attention. 

She loves playing with other dogs her own size (or bigger, too). Savannah does tend to have a bit of a prey drive, so smaller dogs or cats could be an issue. 
She loves dog toys of all kinds. Bones, antlers, and rope toys are great, as they last longer for her! She loves to explore, but is well behaved and at the end of the day lays right down on her dog bed for a snooze. 

Savannah is a very sweet girl. She, especially loves getting attention from her humans. She can be a little shy at first when in a new situation, but her confidence is growing and once she warms up to you, she is very loving and just wants to cuddle. She has a very calm, soothing demeanor--she loves to rest her head on her lap and give little kisses. She hardly jumps on her humans, either! 

Our adoption fee is a $250.00 donation to Pup Squad Animal Rescue. Our adopted dogs are all spayed/neutered, vaccinated and micro-chipped. If you are interested in adoption, please go to www.pupsquad.org/adopt to read more about our policies and find our application. Applications should be submitted to adoption@pupsquad.org or via the online form. 

We are happy to transport our dogs out-of-state as we have lots of experience doing this and love to see our dogs to the best homes possible! We will assist with the whole process to getting your new pet to you. Feel free to email us regarding availability or any other questions. Please remember all breed estimates are just that...estimations based on our experience. 

NOTE: We will only do transport if the dogs are 4 months of age or older as this means they are fully vetted and spay/neutered at this age and ready for transport.

Thank you for choosing to rescue an animal in need!
www.pupsquad.org

animal.description:
Gosh darn it, don’t I just have the cutest little name? My mama done good with that! It matches my cute little face, my cute little rump, and my pretty little eyes. Yup, I’m just a sweet little ‘ol Georgia Peach! True to my Ridgeback instincts I am also very loyal and very protective of the ones I love, so I will need an adult only, low-traffic home where I will be allowed plenty of time to warm up to strangers. I’m young, active, and when I’m in my playgroup I do love playing with the other dogs almost as much as I hate kitty cats! With proper introductions, I may be able to share my home with the correctly matched dog but going to the dog park is a bit more than I can handle. I am already crate trained and housebroken too – Sure, I could use a bit more in the training department, but I’m smart, pick up new things really quickly and am super eager to please my person, so that should be fun! I am lacking in the confidence department so a good confidence boost will do wonders for me! This whole rescue business has my head spinnin’, and I can’t tell which way is up! But I promise, you help me find the surface, and I’ll promise you to be the sweetest companion I can.

5 years old-58lbs. My adoption fee is $200 and includes spay, microchip & registration, 1 month pet health insurance, reduced-cost training class, free vet exam, leash/collar, toy & treat packet, food sample.

PLEASE VISIT https://www.familydogsnewlife.org/policies FOR ADOPTION POLICY/PROCEDURAL INFORMATION

animal.description:
Merlin is a 7 year old, 6 pound neutered male Chihuahua. Merlin can be a VERY difficult chihuahua. He has resource guarding issues and is very nervous and untrusting of anyone. Merlin will eventually allow you to exist in his world, but it took months and months for him to allow his foster mom to show him affection, pick him up, and play with him. He is mostly fine with other small dogs in the home. Merlin’s ideal home will be an adult only home with a fenced yard (he will not be easy to harness). His potential family should understand that Merlin will be extremely difficult to acclimate and it will take several months to gain his trust. He is not a snuggly dog and it's likely you will not be able to pick him up, so patience, understanding, and a willingness to not push his boundaries are a MUST!

**Only very experienced and patient dog people should apply - he has significant behavior issues that you cannot "love away". You will need to respect his boundaries and be okay working around his terms.**

If you wish to be considered for this animal, please download an application at http://fallstonanimalrescue.org/adopt/ or email fallstonrescue@aol.com to request one. It can take up to 2 weeks to process an application; we suggest following up by email on the status if you have not received a reply within 3-5 days. We are an all-volunteer based rescue and we ask for your patience if we are slow to respond. 

Please understand that we fit the dog with the home we feel is best suited and will accept multiple applications on one dog. We have strict requirements for families with children under 10 since many of our dogs are grumpy and may not do well with children. Some dogs will have fence requirements, while others may not.

A pet is a lifetime commitment and it is our duty to do our very best to place them correctly the first time around. We do not take the adoption process lightly. Thank you for choosing to adopt not shop!

animal.description:
Raven is a nice girl who just needs to find the right home for her. She can be shy at first and can startle easily so we need to make sure her new family is dog savvy. She needs a quiet home that is laid back and doesn't have a lot going on so she can spend her golden years relaxed and happy. 

Raven is around 11.5 years of age as of  04/08/20 and does receive a couple of daily medications to help her. 

We think in the right home with the right family where this sweet girl can feel safe, secure and kick back and relax she will be a great companion.

Most of our contact is via email so please keep an eye on your inbox, junk and spam folders.

If you would like to meet this special dog, please email dogs@lunashouse.org to set up an appointment. Please be patient to hear from us as we are all volunteers and may not be able to respond immediately. 

Our volunteers make sure just the right home is chosen for me so they require a home visit. We will occasionally make exceptions on a case by case basis but typically you must live within a 50 mile radius of our location in order to be considered.

The adoption fee is $250 and includes vaccines, flea prevention treatment, neuter/spay, and micro chipping. Like us on Facebook!!

Disclaimer:

Visual breed identification in dogs in unreliable, for most of our dogs we are making the best guess at what the predominant breed or breed mix might be. We get to know each dog as an individual and do our best to describe each dog based on personality and temperament, not breed label.

Ava will not be able to be around other dogs but will be a great and loyal pet for someone who only wants one dog. Ava is willing to learn and very anxious to please people.  She absolutely loves her belly rubbed and ADORES people!


Ava LOVES children but is listed as 'not a good fit' for children only because with her aggression toward other dogs, it is too risky to have children in the house that may leave a door open or a fence gate. Ava needs a very responsible controlled environment with someone who can keep her safe and protect her.

If you would like additional information on Ava, please email us at rufftimesrescueadoptions@gmail.com 

If you are interested in meeting Ava, please go to www.rufftimesrescue.org to fill out a pet of interest form. We will get in touch with you to set a good time for you to meet this sweet loving girl!

animal.description:
Trooper is a magnificent fellow, a mixture of German Shepherd and possibly malamute.  He weighs in at about 80 pounds.  He is discriminating in who he bonds with, so he will need time and patience to establish the trust that he needs with his new owner.  

He walks nicely on the leash and has shown no aggression towards other animals, however, he is not fond of pushy or rough playing dogs.  Trooper is basically a one person dog and would do best with a single individual who prefers a quiet lifestyle without a lot of people coming and going.  He also needs to be the only dog in the household.  

Trooper will guard his home and bark at intruders, therefore, his new owner must be confident and set rules and boundaries for him.  On-going obedience training is required.  He is crate trained, however, he will need some brushing up in that area as well as appropriate behavior.  

Given time, patience and consistency , he would make a top notch and totally loyal companion.   He does know some basic obedience and his desire to please is very high.  Trooper loves physical attention from his chosen person, he is not "everybody's" dog, he reserves his special attention for his selected person

  GEPDA dogs/puppies all come neutered/spayed, micro-chipped, DHPP  shots, a bordetella, and have been de-wormed.  They will have received their first flea treatment before going home.          

We are located in San Martin, CA and we DO NOT  put on any of our dogs/puppies on transport, or shipped to adopters.        

If you are interested in meeting any of our dogs or puppies please our website at http://gepdaus.org/Adoption1.html and fill out an adoption application and forward it to use with your email to ksrottiesrus@gmail.com.         

adoption/donation fee is $250.00 which will have prepared our dogs and or puppies for adoption and to help other rescued dogs with dire medical needs.        

 ***Breed is solely up to the shelter and GEPDA vet.***       

 Learn more about us at our (501c3) website at www.gepdaus.org.
         
Thank you for wanting to save a life!

animal.description:
Billy is a senior and was sadly surrendered with his 'brother', Peppy, to the Arizona Humane Society due to their human entering a care facility.

AHS didn't require that they be pulled together, but given their worlds have recently been turned upside down we thought it was in their best interest to do so. Peppy has since found his forever home, but Billy is still waiting for his perfect family to arrive.

Billy is friendly, housebroken and can use a dog door. He is good with other dogs and supposedly cats but he has not been tested in his foster home. He has been crate trained too. 

Billy's foster has been practicing walking on a leash and he is getting better and better by the day. We love his cute little prance when he walks, because it look like he's on a pogo stick.

Billy does well with other dogs but has a habit of rambunctiously grabbing treats from your fingers when they are offered so we'd recommend a forever home with older children.

During his time in foster care Billy's foster mom noticed his ear thickening. She took him to the vet and he was diagnosed with an aural hematoma.

Aural hematomas often occur when trauma of some sort has happened and the ear respond by filling up with blood. We're not exactly sure how this happened with Billy (maybe he bonked his ear in the doorway coming inside?), but he's fully mended.

Now Billy has one permanent floppy ear, but we think it just adds to his already adorable character!

Interested in learning more about Billy?  Visit MiniMightyMutts.com

animal.description: January 2021--   Maxx is a people-lover!  He's VERY strong and loves to play.  He is kennel trained and does not soil his inside run.  He will sit on command (if you have food) and has learned "stay" for his Kong with some kibble in it.  He's figured out he needs to watch the human and not the treat. Good boy!  He's settled down SOME as a senior dog (10 yrs old) but still has plenty of energy, and plenty of exercise will keep him more settled.  He's developed arthritis in his lower back and has been stiff and painful of a morning during cold weather, despite pain medication and a heat pad under his bedding. He's had laser treatments and injections of Adequan in the past and is on joint supplements. This winter he's not been affected by the arthritis for some reason- yay, Maxx! He gets along well with multiple dogs here.  Please, NO cats, rabbits, squirrels, other small animals, birds, snakes, or garden hoses!  He has a very strong prey drive. He also has a thing about water, like some dogs do-- he wants to catch it (we think) -- from the hose, or as it drips off the roof.  He's been known to zip through a group of people and snatch a mitten off a hand, slick as a whistle.....  He was originally brought to Friends for Life in November 2011 when he was 10 months old when his humans had to move and couldn't keep him. Maxx will add lots of life to YOUR life!  Background check, veterinary reference and 3 personal references required.  If you would like to sponsor Maxx, we need sponsors!  Please contact FFL at wvcompanions@yahoo.com or leave a message at 304 667-1387 and someone will return your call.

animal.description:
PRINCESS came into our program on 2/14/16. She came with her own “Fairy Tale” story that we know will have a “lives happily ever after” ending.
Last December her owner was murdered and she was given to a neighbor to care for in hopes that a relative of her owner would come for her. When no one came for her, the neighbors called animal control to pick her up. She had been waiting at the shelter for several weeks before we were contacted. During that time several of the staff members became attached and worried about her future, as she is blind. We did not hesitate to take her, as we know that we will find that perfect home for her.
We don’t know much about her, other than her owner was a man, and she was hit by a car when she was a puppy which, we are told, caused her blindness. One eye was ruptured and the other has a detached retina. She is approximately a year old, and we are guessing that she may be a Sheltie mix of sorts. We immediately took her to a veterinarian, where it was decided to take out the ruptured eye and spay her at the same time. She is pictured here 3 days after her surgeries.
We do know that she must have been very loved by her owner. She will jump up when you go to pick her up. She loves to be held like a baby and hugs you tightly with her head. She is also not a dog to pity, as she is very self-confident and once she knows the area, you would never know that she is blind. She does, however, need a special home that understands how to be her guide dog in strange places, and her limitations, as she doesn’t want to admit she has any. We are still learning about this little girl, who is about 15 lbs. Princess is in a foster home in Wichita, Kansas and will not be shipped. Requirements to adopt Princess are as follows: Her adopter will have to be in the Wichita Metro area or surrounding area; no out-of-state adopters because we need to do a home visit. A secure fenced yard is a must; invisible fences not acceptable. A veterinarian reference is required showing that your present/past pets are up-to-date on shots, spayed/neutered and on heartworm prevention. Her adoption fee is $200.00. For information on how to apply to adopt Princess, please go to our website www.palsrescue.org

animal.description:
Rainbow is looking for the love of a lifetime!  We have her listed so that we can share her story and perhaps find someone that will understand her needs and have the patience to see her become a wonderful companion dog. There is always hope.
 
I am her foster mom.  She is timid and fearful and although she allows me to touch and pet her, she is a very special case.  She is currently fostered outside in a large dog pen and has run of my backyard at night. I often have other foster dogs and cats/kittens so it is always a busy time for taking care of everyone.  She loves her dog house and comes out sometimes when called. 

She was trapped on the property of a school in Homestead.  We rescued her pups and then trapped her.  She had serious mastitis and needed surgery.  This was 2.5 years ago.  We had a couple of trainers come to my house and work with her.  She does not like the leash although she was able to run alongside a trainer on a bike ride. She loves cheese.  

She has never been fostered inside of a house, though we do think that would change her perception of life.  We have just never found a foster that would accommodate her special personality and be able to spend the time that she needs.  Rainbow has been around my dogs and she has never been assertive or aggressive. She does sometimes bark at the dog next door through the fence.
 
Rainbow weighs about 60 lbs.  She eats well and probably doesn’t get enough exercise.  She is probably about 6/7 years old.
 
Rainbow is not your typical dog.  We do still keep hope in our hearts that someone will come along that will devote time and care to her so she can be the dog that she was born to be.  If you would rather have a dog that is already trusting and ready for adoption, we have others.  

PLEASE SPAY AND NEUTER YOUR DOG!  EMAIL US FOR FREE OR LOW COST RESOURCES.

Donations help us to continue rescuing dogs and cats and helping to make sure that they are healthy and properly socialized before being adopted.Thank you for considering a rescued dog/cat from This Is The Dog!. To donate www.thisisthedog.org
Follow us on Facebook www.facebook.com/thisisthedog 

ADOPTION PROCESS:
1. Email adopt@thisisthedog.org for an application.  Complete Adoption Application and return to us at adopt@thisisthedog.org or fax to 305-247-9127

2. Meet with the dog or cat. Bring treats/toys if you would like.

3. If adoption is approved - Complete Adoption Contract

Adoption Donation - $85 for cats and $200 for dogs.
Out of state cat adoptions are $150 Two for $200
Out of state dog adoptions $300
Pure breed dog adoptions $500

All donations are tax deductible.

Adoption donation for dogs includes Spay/Neuter, Up to Date Vaccines, Microchip,  Deworming, and Heartworm Check if needed.  
Adoption donation for cats/kittens includes Spay/Neuter, Up to Date Vaccines, Deworming, FeLV/FIV testing and Microchip

Thank you! This is the Dog! does not have a shelter. Our dogs and cats are in foster homes primarily in Homestead, FL. We are a small group of volunteers making a difference in the lives of people and the dogs/cats that we help. 

TOUCH a SOUL.  CHANGE a LIFE.  PERHAPS your OWN.

FREE spay/neuter email adopt@thisisthedog.org

This is the Dog! (TITD!) makes no representation, warranty or guarantee about an animal’s breed, temperament or behavior. We also make no representation, warranty, or guarantee as to the size at maturity, health or disposition of any dog because This is the Dog!  is  uncertain of its background or 
history.  Adopter also understands that the dog has displayed no evidence of illness or health problems during its stay with TITD!, unless indicated on the medical history form.

animal.description:
Thank you for your inquiry. Prince has an adopter but we have to wait for them to go pick him up after the stay at home is lifted.  Once he is picked up we will remove his profile. Please do not write to us for an application. Sorry for any inconvenience.


Max is a delightful little guy whose goofy grin and wildly wagging tail get a smile from everyone he meets!  He is housetrained and good with other dogs and cats who are tolerant of dogs.  

Max is about 1-1/2 to 2 years old and about 7 lbs. He is an affectionate, sweet boy. He has blossomed in foster care and has overcome most of his initial shyness at meeting new people. Max thrives in the company of other dogs. He has become play pals with a gentle Aussie and is currently in a foster home with two small dogs. Max has met several horses and was also good with them. 

He would also do well with younger children as long as they treated him gently.    Max absolutely loves his walks! He becomes so excited when he knows that he is going for a walk that he dances on his hind legs (he does the same at meal time!). He has boundless energy while on walks and is well-behaved on the leash.   

At home, Max is a calm and happy dog who loves to cuddle. He'll win your heart when he climbs into your lap and takes a nap while you watch TV. He does not seem interested in playing with toys. He does like to sleep with his person at night and sleeps through the night with no problem.   

Max would do best in a home with another dog (or dogs) or if his person were with him much of the time. He is a special little guy who deserves a stable and loving long-term home.

Max’s adoption fee is $275. He is being fostered in Martinez, CA.

Arrangements to meet our dogs occur after an application has been received.

Please contact us at dogzonerescue@yahoo.com for more information about this great guy or for an application to adopt.

animal.description:
Pearl is a determined spunky little girl with a mind of her own.  She is learning to trust and that she can be safe around people, and it has been amazing to watch her change.  She is affectionate, goofy and very sweet.   She would do well with a patient adult-only family that has another dog (she loves to play with other dogs!) that will keep helping her build up her confidence and be the best dog she can be.  She promises to love you back forever if given that chance.

When I first met her, she was so shy she would not let me take her for a walk. After a little while, she decided I was safe enough to hang out with, so she sat down on the grass next to me, but always keeping the shelter door in her sight.  Great improvement!  Pearl was relaxing a bit and then I realized she was silently TALKING!  You see, when Pearl wants something, she sits and is pointing at it.  Very polite of her! So, we sat like that for a while, chatting, just us girls… Pearl telling me she wanted to go back inside, me telling her it was ok to be outside.  It took a couple of tries and some sweet talk, and she finally let me walk her to the end of the road. Now we stroll around town - you might have seen her fashionably walking up and down Main Street with EXTREMELY good leash manners for the little shy dog that she is. Pearl is around 5 years old.

 I love hanging out with my humans. I like going for walks, hiking, riding in the car, and sitting in your lap. Don't let my size fool you, I am a lap dog and love to cuddle. I like playing with other dog friends and with older children that like to play outside and give me toys. I'm not that fond of babies, however. They are a little too needy and take up too much space. Other than that, I'm pretty easy going and am very smart. I know all of my basic commands and am pretty obedient.

Taco is currently in a foster home while he looks for his forever home; please e-mail trainer@spca914.org to set up a time to meet him. Here are a few fast facts about Taco:

•	He is around 8 years old
•	He's not much of an adventurer, he's more of a homebody and would love a like-minded human companion
•	He's always been a little afraid around people, so he needs someone who will have patience as he gets to know and bond with them (which he will, as you can see from the pics above with his foster fam!)
•	He'd love a nice quiet home for his senior years where he will have security and can feel safe with his people
•	He is housetrained
•	He'd prefer to live with adults only

Reminder: Taco is currently in a foster home while he looks for his forever home, so please e-mail trainer@spca914.org to set up a time to meet him.

Due to Covid-19 the SPCA is allowing adoptions by appointment only. If you’d like to discuss an animal and/or set up a meet and greet please email shelter@spca914.org with your competed application and a copy of your driver’s license or a government issued ID. Please allow up to 72 hours for a response! Thank you for your understanding! 

Adults dogs over 1 year of age: $225-$375
All Puppies: $375
Seniors and Lonely Hearts Club members: $85

Please visit: http://www.spca914.org/adoptanimal.htm to read our Adoption Policy and Procedures in full.

Feel free to e-mail shelter@spca914.org or call (914) 941-2896 ext. 11 with any questions or for more details on the dog(s) in which you are interested.

animal.description:
Shea is searching for a loving family that is experienced with Addison's disease.  Addison's disease can be serious illness BUT dogs who have it do respond well to treatment,and can live normal, healthy, long lives. Shea is now 8 years old and has had Addison's since before he was surrendered to us. 
Besides his illness and his aversion to cats, Shea is a wonderful companion and a terrific family pet. He welcomes all other dogs into his home and loves people, even strangers. He glides along on a leash and loves his walks. Even though a calm home is helpful for his condition, car rides, snuggling, children, and performing tricks are also high on his list of enjoyable activities. 


ADOPTION FEE:$150

animal.description:
My name is Moose! I am a 9 year old Black Shepherd/ Pit Bull Mix. I am a big guy with a big heart! I'm a little shy and "barky" upon meeting new people, but once I warm up, I love to roll over for belly rubs. This part of my personality also makes me one amazing guard dog. I also get along great with kids and other dogs, especially female ones, and I love treats of any kind and getting attention! I'm a mellow guy and don't require a lot of exercise, and am perfectly happy to just be with my people. 

I am unfortunately allergic to many things including grass. I would do best in a house with mostly concrete. I do like to play ball, so that would be cool also.

I was found as a stray under a freeway over pass by the All Paws Rescue's founder who just couldn't leave me behind. I've been waiting for my forever family for quite awhile now, and would love to find a forever family of my own. Please ask to meet me because I'm sure once you get to know me, you will fall in love with me.

If you're interested in meeting or adopting me, please go to our website and fill out an adoption application. I am currently being fostered in Chino, CA. My adoption fee is $150. http://www.allpawsrescue-rehab.org/#!adoptable-dogs/c1hor

animal.description: Clementine is an Australian Shepherd/Redbone Hound mix who was born in August 2015. She weighs about 30 lbs.  Clem has a medical condition called megaesophagus. Dogs with megaesophagus have a dilated esophagus due to lack of muscle tone, which causes food to sit in the esophagus rather than travel to the stomach. As a result, it is not unusual for her to regurgitate.  She is on a structured feeding routine and eats in a Bailey Chair. In spite of this, Clementine is an otherwise ‘normal' dog. She is very friendly with everyone – including other dogs and cats – and especially loves children. She is housebroken and crate trained. Clem’s megaesophagus will be a lifelong medical condition that will need continued monitoring.  She is an incredibly sweet dog and would love to be part of a family.

animal.description: PEG:  Peg is an estimated 3-4 years old and weighs @ 45 lbs.  She is very clean in her kennel so we think she would be great indoors.  She is not destructive, does not jump up and doesn't bark unless there is something to bark about.  Peg came to us from a situation where she was used fro breeding purposes and her needs and comfort were not met.  Upon arrival she was very distrustful and frightened of our volunteers, shrinking in the back of her kennel.  She was not aggressive toward us but  unsure about us.  We worked with her daily to gain her trust and day by day she has responded.  For the first time in her life she has enjoyed playing with balls, squeaky toys, tummy rubs and the affection of humans.  She now greets us with her tail wagging eager to get out for potty and play time.  She is still cautious with strangers but warms up quickly.  Peg has come so far and it has been heartwarming to watch her bloom.  She will make someone a wonderful, loyal companion.  She will need a patient owner who will allow time for bonding.

Here is our new girl, Iris. She was hit by a car and has a broken pelvis. She was taken to the shelter where they put her on the EU list. 

We came and got her and took her straight to the vet for care. Her pelvis is healing very nicely and she will be spayed in the coming weeks.

Iris is current on all her shots and has been chipped. She is good with other dogs as we have seen with her foster.
Iris is full of energy and feeling good.
 She is in great spirits and is a happy girl. 

Iris is approx 3 yr old and still a puppy that will need a strong handler because she is a strong girl.  She loves her toys and loves belly rubs.

She is currently in the DFW area so if you are interested in her, please fill out our application. A home check and vet check is required. 

Her perfect home will have a 6' fenced in yard as she can jump a 4' fence and no cats.

Will you be her forever home?
Please ask about Iris when you contact Blue Angel Weimaraner Rescue of Texas. 

For donations, please send via paypal to: blueangelweims@att.net Phone: (469) 844-0425 www.blueangelweimaranerrescueoftexas.org.  We gratefully accept donations of any amount to help our beautiful gray & blue friends in need. We are an all-volunteer, 501(c)(3) non-profit, charitable organization. Donations are tax-deductible as allowed by law. Our rescue Weimaraners are current on all vaccinations and heartworm preventative. They are spayed or neutered, and microchipped.

animal.description:
As a puppy, Daisy was surrendered to a kill shelter along with her mother and 6 siblings. Daisy was adopted as a puppy, and all was well at first. Until it wasn't. Daisy was surrendered back to us as the family had to move and it was disclosed at the time that a member of the family had abused Daisy. It was a male so she is wary of men at first. 

We are guessing there is Beagle and Foxhound in her background.  Daisy weighs about 35 pounds and is about 4 years old.  She prefers females but warms up to men who are patient and she is not suitable in a home with children.  She needs a nice big FENCED yard because she likes to run. Daisy is good with most dogs when properly introduced. She needs a patient adopter that will take it slow and earn her trust. Maybe come out and visit her a few times to let her learn who you are, then maybe work from there. Nothing worthwhile ever comes easy. And Daisy is a doll and quite the character once you are in her circle. Hot dogs help! 

Adoption fee: (Cash/Check) $175 (Credit/Debit) $180.  This includes vet care and vaccines up until adoption, spaying/neutering, and microchip. If you have questions about an animal, please complete an adoption application at sqrescueinc.org  FIRST.  Someone will reach out to you once you are approved and be able to answer all your questions. Your application must be approved prior to meeting our dogs. Missing or incomplete information will delay processing of applications.  For questions about the application process, you may call 803.223.9729 and leave a message.

To access the home page for our group, click on Southern Comfort Maltese Rescue which will take you to the map page.  Below the map is our logo and the link to click on to access adoption forms, contact info or to donate. ALL DONATIONS ARE TAX DEDUCTIBLE.


We have a special angels for SissyGirl!!!  Concetta Fisher and Elizabeth Ashe!!  SCMR thanks you and so does SissyGirl.



Update Sept. 2018

SissyGirl is still sweet as can be, but her physical condition is deteriorating. She has a form of myelopathy which is causing her to lose the use of her back legs. She has to be carried outside several times a day to potty. Otherwise, she lounges on a pee pad in her favorite bed where she can see everyone and what all is going on.  

She's still very interested in all the activity around her. She used to be very enthusiastic about her food, but her lack of activity may have affected her appetite. She has to be spoon fed like a baby now. She will eat as long as it's soupy, and she is well nourished with good bowel function.  

We believe this little angel is in her twilight. It might depress her to have to relocate as she nears the end of life stage, and she could continue to live for a long time interested in all around her. Also, her physical disability might affect her negatively...we don't know.  

Most people aren't interested in adopting a hospice dog, and that is understandable. However, you can help by becoming a sponsor for SissyGirl and helping us pay for her ongoing care. Please become one of SissyGirl's Angels now, and help us help her!


NOTE: SCMR DOES NOT adopt to homes with children under the age of 10 years or homes with Electric Fences

Out-of-state adoptions are possible; however, the approved adoptive home is responsible for making the necessary arrangements to pick up their new little one.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

MEET ROXY 5!! **Please Note: This is a courtesy post for another rescue; different adoption fees/policy apply.

     Roxy is a happy, loving girl who loves attention and could be pet all day! She smiles -- so cute.  

  Roxy loves the park, swimming, and desert walks. She's very friendly and likes people, dogs, and children. She plays fetch and loves tennis balls, toys, and shredding things (put your shoes away!).  

  Due to Roxy's physical strength and lack of leash training, she needs a strong, active owner who will help her with further training. She knows basic commands (come, no, sit) but she often ignores them if she is distracted.  

  Roxy is beginning to understand "stay, heel, no bark, and stop" but needs additional training. Roxy has a tendency to happily bark as people walk by, and we are currently working on that. She responds very well to positive reinforcement, such as "Good girl, no bark!" as she very much wants to please.  

  Roxy may display protective reactions around the home area and is a good watchdog. She has learned a lot in short period of time, wants to be where you are and is a  good friend and companion! 

  Due to obesity, Roxy 5  requires strict  diet, thyroid medication,  and exercise daily. 

 

 For more information or to meet this pet, please complete an application or send email to info@underdogaz.com

  If you're reading this via a pet-search site, please view this pet's page  at www.UnderdogAZ.com/animals  for more photos and details.

animal.description:
Courtesy listing! please contact Nelly at hon3y24@hotmail.com or via phone at 323-503-6402.  Thank you.

Tripod Tinker Bell was rescued by a Good Samaritan, Nelly in June 2015 from a very bad situation. She was starved and emaciated at that time, and eventually had to have her back left leg amputated due to severe neglect by her previous owner.  Ms. Tinker Bell does not see herself as a handicapped furry however, as she still gets around perfectly fine.  In fact, being a very happy tripod has actually gotten her extra love and attention by everyone she meets which she always enjoys!  Tinker Bell is a sunny and cheery girl who's smile is contagious.

Tinker Bell is approx. 3 years old with beautiful green eyes, has 1 amputated leg, spayed, current on vaccinations, not microchipped, 45 pounds, housetrained and crate trained.  She adores people and kids but is dog selective so a proper meet and greet is needed. She is healthy as a bug, loves car rides and walks, and to play with squeaky toys.  Tinker Bell is a jumper...yes, even as a tripod!... so an 8' fence is a requirement but doesn't have any bad habits like barking, chewing or digging.  Any chance she gets, she'll want to snuggle up to you and give tons of affection and kisses. 

If you think Tinker Bell will be a perfect fit within your family and would like to meet her in person, or have any other questions about her, please contact Nelly at hon3y24@hotmail.com or via phone at 323-503-6402.  Thank you.

She is now about 5 years old and  about 50-55 pounds.  She is spayed, micro chipped and up to date with her shots.

animal.description:
My name is Trudy. My rescue mom named me that because as soon as she pulled up & opened her car door I jumped in there so fast! My rescue mom always tells everybody I was like an intruder- but, the good kind! Hence my name, Trudy! 

To be honest, I was just so happy to have someone notice me. I’d been running the streets and I was getting worried & more scared by the day. I found it really hard to be alone with nowhere to feel safe. But, anyway...

I am an 80 pound Doberman mix. I’m a lot of fun & full of energy! I really love walks & could play all day- if it’s with you or other fun dogs! But, I want you to know that I’m great at vegging-out on the couch on a lazy weekend, too. The thing is, I need someone or a whole family to do these things with. Seriously, you’d never look back as soon as I come into your life! “What was our life even like before Trudy?!”

Here’re some of Trudy's attributes:
-- Doggie door trained
-- Leash trained
-- Loves riding in the car
-- Highly curious

animal.description:
Tracy is a very sweet, happy, female Boston Terrier/AmStaff mix.  She is approx. 12 years old, weighs about 45 pounds, is short & stocky, and has adorable ears that flop over when she perks them up.  She loves to go on leisurely walks and sniff all the interesting scents.  She walks well on a lead, but at times can pull a little bit.  She loves to cuddle and have her ears scratched, but prefers not to share her human(s) with other dogs, so she sometimes gets jealous if her canine housemates try to encroach on her cuddle time.  She would be fine as an only dog or living in a home with other calm dogs (more assertive dogs can make her a little bit snippy).

Tracy is a lower energy gal who loves Nylabones and would much rather snooze on a comfy sofa or dog bed, than play with other dogs!  She is afraid of storms and fireworks, and hasn’t been cat tested so we're not sure if she can live in a home with cats.  She does not currently live in a foster home with children, but she likes when kids pet her at adoption events.  Tracy is housebroken, crate trained, spayed, fully vaccinated, And microchipped. 

If you have additional questions about Tracy, please email us at info@barkvilledogresscue.org.  If you'd like to adopt Tracy, please submit an adoption application at www.barkvilledogrescue.org.

animal.description:
Queenie is a spectacular pet in need of a home experienced with German Shepherds.   5-6 years old in age, she is a protective girl who is not very stranger tolerant, so the meet-and-greet procedure with her must be more drawn out and she belongs only in a home comfortable with not allowing strangers to make direct contact with their dog.  Other than that, she is pretty close to perfect.  She can be in public settings where strangers are respectfully hands off.  Approximately four years old, she was pulled from a high kill shelter in Texas heavily pregnant and successfully raised a litter of puppies while being a wonderful mom.  She is now ready to move onto a forever ending of her own :)  She is purebred, although her ears did fail to stand, and a real deal GSD.   She is GREAT company - very playful, joyful and extremely affectionate.  If a German Shepherd can be merry, that would be her.  She is highly intelligent (both the good and the bad....she is an escape artist who can range from smart to daring), very responsible, forms a strong bond, and is an energetic girl with an extremely playful and fun personality.   For the breed, she is not a noisy dog, does great with other dogs, and is ok around cats. Older children only, please, as toddlers make her nervous.  

THE RIGHT HOME for Queenie needs to have breed experience.  Queenie is territorial and protective by her nature.  When displaced, she forms a strong bond, but meet-and-greets will require patience and understanding as she is not receptive to strangers.  This is a higher energy girl who belongs with someone active.  She crates well and is overall a good housedog, but if bored and under stimulated will be destructive.  She will do fine in a home with another  dog and has learned not to bother cats, but she should not be around smaller children - they are very foreign to her and she finds their movements unsettling.  If you need a dog who can thrive in social settings, she is not the dog for you as while she can be socialized better with strangers, her social circle being an elite group of knowns is inherent to both her and the breed itself.  If, however, you seek a adventurous companion, up for anything, who bonds strongly and is extremely loyal, she could be the dog for you.

Applications are available via contacting Lucy at maramuser@gmail.com.  Her adoption fee is $450.

animal.description:
Hello there! I’m India and I am lobbying for a home of my own. It’s been a long-term goal of mine and I’m here to enlist your help! So, sit still for a moment and read all about me!

I’m a Pointer/Brittany Spaniel mix and, as you can tell from my candid photos, I’m quite the gorgeous girl.

In addition to my stunning good looks, I also have a fabulous personality! I’m fun and energetic and also a very, very good listener. I think I'd like to be your one and only pet, if you don't mind. Don't worry--I'll be all you ever need!

Want to pet me? Because I like being petted, but I loooooove to have my ears and belly rubbed.

If you need some testimonials, I can tell you right now that I’m a volunteer favorite and have admirers that come to run with me and take me for car rides (another one of my very favorite activities!).

I also like to carry my toy around in my mouth, which, in addition to having a utilitarian function (they have to get from one place to another, right?) also is irresistibly adorable.

If you like to go for walks or runs, or like to ride in the car, or like to give ear and belly rubs, come on out and meet me so we can get down to business and make sure I’m a good fit for your family!

Please call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 if you are smitten and want to learn more!

Please contact The Pet Connection if you can foster, adopt, or sponsor a special needs dog or cat. 913-671-7387 call or text. www.thepetconnection.net. 

The Pet Connection is a membership organization  operating a no-kill adoption center located at 417 N Rawhide Suite H, Olathe, KS 66061.

Appointments can be made to meet an animal by calling us at (913) 671-PETS.        

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
Prior to adoption, our animals are:  
**Tested for diseases 
**Vaccinated 
**Spayed/neutered 
**Microchipped  

ADOPTION INFORMATION: - NO COST adoptions with an encouraged donation are accepted for adoption.

The Pet Connection also offers adopters FREE veterinary examination and a    medical care support plan for 60 days after adoption, as well as lifetime behavioral training, safe sanctuary for pets returned in emergency situations, extensive assistance with lost and found pets, and  other expert pet services in a variety of areas, including pet selection, behavioral issues, general training, nutrition, and transition to adoptive homes.

She will need a patient family, like her foster family, who has done miracles bringing her out of her shell. 

If you would like to make Demi part of your family, please go to:  https://goo.gl/forms/PkzEp1Id67UG1mDl2 and complete an online application to adopt.  Remember, reference checks and home visits apply to all Im-Paws-Able dogs, but especially to special girls like Demi!!!

Noah's Arks Rescue is all about giving an Abused Animal a second chance at life and to experience what true love is. We take animals that have been tortured, abused, and neglected and supply the emergency medical care required to get them well. We then provide rehab physically and mentally to prepare them for their new home and new life. We are located in Ridgeland, SC., and are by appointment only. All of our dogs are at our Rehabilitation Center either in hospice care or being loved on by staff until we find them forever homes. Please call 843.540.6755 or email NoahsArksRescues@mac.com with any questions. If you are interested, please fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.noahs-arks.net/nar-application. We do adopt out of state and will arrange transports. Our dogs are not allowed to fly cargo at any time.

animal.description:
Albert was found by a good samaritan wandering around an alley scrounging for food. He was thin and frightened. Luckily, he was taken in and provided with food and a warm bed. Albert was grateful and quickly took to his rescuer. Albert is now waiting for a forever home and hopes to find one before the holidays this year!
Albert is learning his manners. He is doing pretty well for a pup who isn't used to following anyone else's rules! He can sit and walk well on the leash. Albert will do pretty much anything for a treat. Albert is a little insecure and takes some warming up to new people. Who can blame him, being treated poorly and left alone. Nobody had ever given Albert a reason to trust them and he is trying to learn how to feel safe with people. Once he feels safe, he is a most loyal companion!
Give this beautiful pup reason to smile again, be himself again, be free of fear and worry, and live the life meant for a dog as amazing as him

Albert is available for private party adoption through his respective owner. Saving Grace Pit Bull Rescue (SGPBR) is assisting in helping his owner find an adoptive home by listing him here. His owner does not represent SGPBR. Albert is not owned by or associated with SGPBR, including SGPBR's adoption and foster programs. SGPBR has not evaluated Albert and makes no claims regarding temperament/disposition and behavior. All information provided is from the owner. SGPBR has not generated or substantiated any information above. SGPBR does verify that all dogs in the courtesy listing program are current on vaccinations and spayed/neutered. 

If you are interested in Albert, we can put you in direct contact with the owner directly for additional information. You may utilize SGPBR's online adoption application as a guideline/tool for providing information to the owner, but all inquiries should go through the dog's owner directly. If you choose to use Saving Grace's application, Saving Grace will foward your application submission to the owner. Thanks!

Malone and his sister Marla are almost 4 years old and so readto find their forever home.   We believe them to be Anatolian Shepherd, Boxer, Lab, Husky, Pug blends with possibly a little Poodle thrown in for good measure.   Whatever their breed, one thing is for sure they are smart, playful and fun.  He and Marla came to us with their mother and their 8 siblings when they were 12 weeks old.  So basically these wonderful dogs have grown up in our rescue and together and we could not bare to separate them.  Malone absolutely adores children, if you ask her kids are his favorite for sure.  She plays wonderful with other dogs as well as cats. He warms up quicker to new people compared to Marla and he really is a support system for her.  Malone is crate and potty trained to a doggie door.  It would be best for them to go to home with a fenced in yard.

Meet our GYPSY girl <3 <3 <3

This sweet girl was dumped over the summer and based on her behavior, she was also probably kept outside, living on the end of a leash for a very long time and not at all socialized :-(.

We've been working with her and she is blossoming into a super loving, playful, energetic and smart girl. She really is wonderful and every time we think we couldn't love her more, she looks at us with that goofy smile and we just melt.

Gypsy is a 2.5 year old Pit Bull mix, is spayed, UTD on shots and micro chipped. She gets along great with dogs but a meet and greet is a must. However, she does not want to share her home with cats or small kids.

If you are meant for her, please come to the AWSOM shelter in Stroudsburg, PA, any day, from 11-4. Gypsy is a work in progress...but aren't we all?!

Age of Dog: Approx. 2.5 years

All of our adult dogs at AWSOM are spayed or neutered and fully vaccinated prior to adoption. AWSOM will pay for puppies to be spayed and neutered when they are old enough and that is covered by our adoption fee. We will honestly represent our animals to the public. We welcome you to come to our facility to meet our dogs. Thank you so very much for thinking adoption. If you would like to meet this pet or get more information, please visit http://www.awsomanimals.org/adoptablepets/adoptionprocess.html or call 570-421-3647.

animal.description:
I was sitting in the LAST CALL room at Broward Animal Control when my number was called but not to be euthanized but to be spared death and given a new chance at life.  

Original story...Originally names T Bone...renamed Nerites for his lovely obsession with water ...and also the lover of Aphrodite.. and a lover he is. CHANGED TO NEMO

He didnt answer to his former name and perhaps a new start with a new name will bring this beautiful boy great adventures with an owner that will keep him FOREVER!

This boy had a home in Miami Dade county since a small pup, but was forced to leave  by a disgruntled neighbor who called MDAS...and he was sent to an unknown, unchecked foster who placed him in BCAC due to him "nor liking her", needless to say that twit caused his near death when we took him out of the "end of the line " room of BCAC.

We took him with the hopes to reunite him legally with his family, however when told we could  possibly do this, the response was not what we had hoped and therfore he belongs with someone  who will go the distance to have him. He is worth at least that!

He was born May 3rd 2013  and is housebroken and such a good boy. However he is OBSESSED with water and an amazing swimmer. So if you have a pool.. he will get out on his own, from any side, however trying to stop him from going in is more of the issue and having him stay out is as well ...so if you have a pool be prepared to go in after him to get him out. Check out his own Facebook page   "NEMO the swimming pit "   He has crazy strong swimming skills!

To adopt contact www.misfitresq.org  Provide a phone number as well. 

All dogs are spayed or neutered, chipped and vaccinated as well on current flea and hw prevention. Many are crate trained but he doesnt need one.

animal.description:
This handsome guy is one of a huge litter DCAWS agreed to take from the shelter in Houston County when they were overloaded with intake.  He was adopted when a young puppy.  In early June we received a call from an animal facility in St. Louis reporting that he was with them.  He had been brought in for observation at the age of 3-1/2 years because he had nipped a child.  When the 10 days were up he was not reclaimed by the family.  
Report from the facility is that this was a play nip and there were no ER or medical or police reports filed as this was a minor and non-vicious incident.  Since his return Scooter has been in a home with several other dogs and is doing well there.  He has shown himself to be affectionate, smart, playful and certainly of good nature, although he does still nip in play occasionally.  He is in need of a new home where he is corrected with training and is never abandoned again.
Born 12/25/12

animal.description:
Merci' (French for thank you) has been waiting for the right home. She is now going on 6 years old. She will ONLY be adopted to someone who has a rural setting, she gets to wound up with traffic and people going by. Merci’ has a tendency to eat things she shouldn’t and has had one surgery to remove an item, she needs to be in a home that will be up to speed on this.
She also needs a fenced yard.
She was living in an outdoor pen most of the time, had few manners and is still in training. Gets along with large more easy going dogs or those who will put her kindly in her place. She could use a good mentor dog. No cats or smaller dogs. 
She's still getting weight on but turning into quite a pretty girl.
Needs continued training. Knows sit and learning to chill.
Must have a fenced yard and a knowledgeable large dog owner who has the time and patience to continue to help her blossom.
Indoor, loving, lifetime homes only. Children over 10 may be OK, she is real bouncy so no little ones.
Ton of potential.
Email alterupet@aol.com to inquire.
Please look over the criteria before inquiring.

animal.description:
PUPDATE 16 April 2020: The decision has been made that it is in the best interest for Syd to live out her life here. She will be considered a sanctuary dog and will be cared for as we care for our personal dogs.
PUPDATE 26 April 2019: Yes, Syd is still here. Sadly, the experience she went through while in placement have made her difficult to rehome, so she will remain here until the perfect human for her is found.
Syd is truly afraid of children and strangers. While she is lovely with people that she knows, she is fearful of the unknown and is pro-active in her reactive behaviour to protect herself. While we have found her to be easy to manage, her people must be diligent and advocate for her.
Syd's perfect home would be a woman who loves to train and enjoys having her dog with her a lot. She would have a fenced yard and an outdoor kennel for when her person is away. Syd would LOVE to be an on-leash hiking partner and would truly thrive being part of a small pack and enjoying her people.
PUPDATE 19 May 2017: Syd had been adopted, and was returned to us, as she was not managed appropriately in her home, and she became reactive to people entering the home. On return to the farm, we have worked with her and found that she quickly returned to appropriate behaviour when managed appropriately. Syd is currently in 'board and train' with our trainer on grounds.
Syd will do best in a calm, multi-dog home that is interested in classes and continued learning for their dogs.
*********
There's not much Syd couldn't do with the right person to partner with. She is currently picking up agility like a pro, and is eager to learn. Sid will do best in a home with another dog, and a human willing to fill her head with stuff. Syd needs moderate exercise to be happy here, though she does have other dogs to play with.

Please read our procedures prior to making inquiry regarding this dog. 

Please go to our main website at www.mabcr.org for more information regarding the adoption of this or any dog from our rescue. 

Please note that while this dog is currently available, any dog on our site may have an adoption pending and may not be available to you at this time. The same dog may later become available if the adoption falls through. 

Our website www.mabcr.org will give you details on our adoption procedures as well as an application for adoption. An application must be submitted prior to 'matching' an adopter with a dog as all dogs do not fit into all homes. We pride ourselves in our adoption process, we take the time to get to know our adopters so that we can place a dog with them that they can enjoy for years to come.

Please understand that we will not discuss dogs with individual adopters until after the application process is completed.

Our rescue does not have a public facility, therefore there are no visiting hours. Appointments to visit with the available dogs are made after the application process has been completed by our staff.  

To assist any dog within the MABCR organization, please consider making a donation to the general fund or to the medical fund. All dogs coming into our rescue are fully vetted (s/n and innoculations) prior to adoption.

Rescuing animals is quite expensive. If you are unable to adopt, but would like to help this, or any other animal in our system, please consider a sponsorship donation. 
For information on our sponsorship program, please contact Sarah at SLR@mabcr.org. 

 DONATE ONLINE USING PAYPAL

Thank you for your interest in Mid-Atlantic Border Collie Rescue.
